{#
  themeChooserCustom — a thin wrapper around the shipped themeChooser
  macro that bakes in a house glyph.

  This used to be a FORK of theme-chooser.njk, because the old macro
  did not inspect `caller`. That is no longer true: the shipped macro
  supports `{% call %}` directly, and the block body replaces the
  default `<span class="theme-chooser-icon">` INSIDE the button.
  Everything else — the root <div>, the hidden input, the button's
  ARIA attributes, and the <ul role="listbox"> with its options — is
  still rendered by the shipped macro, so the keyboard contract and
  the data-lily-* hooks keep working.

  Wrapping is the useful pattern when a project wants one icon
  everywhere: call this macro instead of themeChooser and every
  instance gets the same glyph, without repeating the `{% call %}`
  block at each call site.

  The glyph MUST be aria-hidden (plus focusable="false" on SVG): the
  button is icon-only, so its accessible name has to keep coming from
  aria-label alone.

  Note this replaces the glyph only. It does not — and cannot —
  change the option markup; the caller block no longer renders
  options at all.
#}
{%- from "../theme-chooser.njk" import themeChooser -%}

{%- macro themeChooserCustom(opts) -%}
{%- call themeChooser(opts) -%}
<svg class="my-theme-glyph" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"
     aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
  <circle cx="8" cy="8" r="7" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
  <path d="M8 1a7 7 0 0 1 0 14z" fill="currentColor"/>
</svg>
{%- endcall -%}
{%- endmacro -%}
